{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/tools/refactor","identifier":"CASNamespaceSpecs","question":"Which CAS namespace names does CASNamespaceSpecs return? I need to know whether generated pr refactor instructions can reasonably refer to docs-add, dry, test-cleanup, and test-ensure-coverage as CAS namespaces.","answer":"`CASNamespaceSpecs` returns CAS specs only for refactors with `casPolicyCodeUnit`.\n\nCurrent returned specs are:\n\n- `Name: \"refactor-dry\"`, `Version: 1`, `HashMode: gocas.HashModeCodeUnit`\n- `Name: \"refactor-test-cleanup\"`, `Version: 1`, `HashMode: gocas.HashModeCodeUnit`\n- `Name: \"refactor-test-ensure-coverage\"`, `Version: 1`, `HashMode: gocas.HashModeCodeUnit`\n\nUsing `gocas.NamespaceSpec.Namespace()`, those versioned filesystem namespace strings should be:\n\n- `refactor-dry-1`\n- `refactor-test-cleanup-1`\n- `refactor-test-ensure-coverage-1`\n\n`docs-add` is registered as a refactor, but its `casPolicy` is `casPolicyIgnore`, so `CASNamespaceSpecs` does not return a CAS namespace for it. Same for `docs-fix` and `docs-improve-from-clarify`.\n\nSo: generated PR/refactor instructions should not refer to `docs-add` as a CAS namespace. For the others, prefer the exact CAS namespace names `refactor-dry`, `refactor-test-cleanup`, and `refactor-test-ensure-coverage` or the versioned namespace strings with `-1`, rather than the bare refactor names."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1779278986,"paths":["internal/tools/refactor/SPEC.md","internal/tools/refactor/doc.go","internal/tools/refactor/presentation.go","internal/tools/refactor/refactor.go","internal/tools/refactor/refactor_test.go"],"git_clean":false,"git_commit":"4ad72bf5345180b39453052f57f63b88a4fca025","git_merge_base":"2b0a1dd5348717b9bad1dee1595463f516e5b39e"}}